title: BsSndRpt - Expected argument 'c'
body: Since the patch a day ago, I get an error message when I try to launch the game. The window is titled "BsSndRpt" and it says "Expected argument 'c'". I restarted my computer and reinstalled the game and it didn't help.

replies.body: i got the same thing this morning. Anyone has a fix?

I was struggling with the same problem after I did a system restore on my computer. However, I fixed it after an hour.

Go to Riot Games > League of Legends
Scroll down and you should see

Lol Client (The new client)
lol.launcher.admin (old client)
lol.launcher (old client)

Right click and delete the NEW client. Go to your recycling bin and delete it completely.

Even though you deleted the NEW client your computer, you should still have the 
League of Legends icon (new client) on your desktop.

Double click it and it should install the recent patch.
That's what I did and it's working fine now.

This is likely caused by some corrupt files inside your League directory. I'd like you to grab our [**Hextech Repair Tool**](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/224826367) and check the box for *Force Repatch* before hitting the **Start** button. After the process finishes, launch League as admin (right-click, *run as admin*) and let me know if this worked for you or not.
